    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10901.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Russian Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Russian Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor in behalf of
                    the Imperial Government to request the extradition of Jan Janov Pouren, a
                    Russian subject, charged with murder, robbery, and attempted murders, and now at
                    New York, where he lives under the name of W. Kohks, alias Martin Martinson.</p>
                <p>The above man’s criminal record is in the hands of the consul general of Russia
                    at New York who, as agent of the Imperial Government <pb facs="0586" n="514"
                        xml:id="pg_514"/> at New York, has charge of the proceedings before the
                    local authorities.</p>
                <p>Be pleased, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rosen.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
